FBIS3-16764 "drsov054_b_94020" FBIS-SOV-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Zhirinovskiy Says Situation To `Deteriorate' LD1903130794 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1230 GMT 19 Mar 94 LD1903130794 Moscow 2x2 Television Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The leader of the State Duma Liberal-Democratic Party of Russia [LDPR] faction Vladimir Zhirinovskiy considers that the country's political situation will deteriorate sharply in April. Speaking today at the eighth regional party conference in Moscow, he suggested that unconstitutional actions would again be undertaken. Vladimir Zhirinovskiy is convinced that the LDPR will be victorious at the presidential elections. In his opinion, neither the Communists nor the new Zorkin-Rutskoy coalition nor any other opposition politicians have any chance of winning today.
